mes of India|date=6 September 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nKaur started her career at the young age of 5, by playing the character of Prachi in the 2009 series ''[[Jhansi Ki Rani (2009 TV series)|Jhansi Ki Rani]]''.<ref name=bbb>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-06-10/tv/29653065_1_show-grades-study |author=Amrita Mulchandani |title=I enjoy the media attention: Ashnoor Kaur |newspaper=The Times of India |date=10 June 2011 |accessdate=9 September 2010 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120707200407/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-06-10/tv/29653065_1_show-grades-study |archivedate=7 July 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/tv/news/hindi/ashnoor-kaur-and-anirudh-dave-complete-a-decade-in-the-industry/articleshow/68116271.cms|title=Ashnoor Kaur and Anirudh Dave complete a decade in the Industry|last=|first=|date=|website=The Times Of India|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> She later played Navika Vyas Bhatnagar in the television series ''[[Na Bole Tum Na Maine Kuch Kaha]]'' and  ''[[Na Bole Tum Na Maine Kuch Kaha 2]]''. She also acted as young Mayra Kapoor in the show ''[[Bade Achhe Lagte Hain]]''. She appeared in  ''[[C.I.D. (Indian TV series)|CID]]'', and as Ashok Sundari in the mythological series, ''[[Devon Ke Dev...Mahadev]]''.<ref name=ccc>{{cite news|title=Ashnoor Kaur to enter Mahadev |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-10-30/tv/34816577_1_sonarika-bhadoria-ashnoor-kaur-devon-ke-dev-mahadev |newspaper=The Times of India |date=30 October 2012 |accessdate=3 November 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130103100008/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-10-30/tv/34816577_1_sonarika-bhadoria-ashnoor-kaur-devon-ke-dev-mahadev |archivedate=3 January 2013 }}</ref> She had the role of young Naira Singhania in [[Yeh Rishta Kya Kehlata Hai]].<ref name=eee>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/new